title: [Gyldemar Forest, Blasted Heath]
description: Wind has formed a sea of grey ash dunes.  A few blackened limbs lie scattered across the desert, while large rocks barely peak through the ash.  One rock appears to have been sheared in half by some tremendous force.

Wind has formed a sea of grey ash dunes, now a pale grey in the sparkle of the moonlight.  A few blackened limbs lie scattered across the desert, while large rocks barely peak through the ash.  One rock appears to have been sheared in half by some tremendous force.
